<tag name="PERSON" value="start"/>Such<tag name="PERSON" value="end"/> was <tag name="PERSON" value="start"/>Zevi<tag name="PERSON" value="end"/>'s uncompromising critique of any tendency in modern architecture towards classicism that he even would criticize those architects he otherwise admired: "When <tag name="PERSON" value="start"/>Gropius<tag name="PERSON" value="end"/>, <tag name="PERSON" value="start"/>Mies<tag name="PERSON" value="end"/> and <tag name="PERSON" value="start"/>Aalto<tag name="PERSON" value="end"/> produced [symmetrical buildings] it was an act of surrender. Lacking a modern code, they weakened and regressed to the familiar womb of classicism." (<tag name="PERSON" value="start"/>Zevi<tag name="PERSON" value="end"/>, <tag name="MISC" value="start"/>The Modern Language of Architecture<tag name="MISC" value="end"/>).
